                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.20/735: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-18T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 18, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. Press dispatches earlier in day give account of Simon’s speech in Commons
                    about note<note n="38" xml:id="d231fn38">British Cmd. 4848, Germany No. 1
                        (1935): <hi rend="italic">Note Delivered by His Majesty’s, Ambassador in
                            Berlin to the German Government on Maxell 18, 1935</hi>.</note> to
                    Germany. Very important that we should know nature of it as we are without any
                    background or other official information from London for our guidance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
